File: Government continues to urge South Africans to take precautions and adhere to preventative measures. JOHANNESBURG - Correctional Services deputy minister Nkosi Phathekile Holomisa has tested positive for the coronavirus. He's self-isolating at home and reportedly in good spirits. READ: SA's COVID-19 cases jump by 10000 in five days Government continues to urge South Africans to take precautions and adhere to preventative measures. These include wearing a mask, social distancing, and washing hands regularly with soap or sanitiser that contains 70 percent alcohol. The public has also been advised to continue avoiding crowded places and seek medical attention if symptoms such as fever, cough and difficulty breathing are experienced. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.